ya'll think about the hate crimes legislation?  Do you think we should have special categories and/or punishments for crimes that are committed based on bigotry of some kind?  Should it make a difference if someone vandalizes your car just because it's there and he's drunk, or if he does it because you're Jewish and he doesn't like 'your kind'?  Should there be stiffer penalties for breaking a mosque's window than breaking a store window?<br>
<br>
I go back and forth on this.. I'd like to hear other POVs.<br>
<br>
Kate <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luvthatdyl>LuvThatDyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/13/03 5:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Hate Crimes?</span><hr size=1> Personally, I'm against hate crime legislation.  This is one issue that I agree with our idiot president about.  I feel that any violent crime is a hate crime, and that people should be punished based off the crime itself as opposed to the motive.  My husband is a white heterosexual male who labels himself as a Presbyterian.  If he was walking down the street next to a black-Jewish homosexual, and one guy beat up my husband while another guy beat up the black-Jewish homosexual, then I would want both men to get the same punishment.  Just because my husband is in the majority, it doesn't mean he doesn't deserve the same protection as minorities.  I also don't expect special treatment for having a Jewish background.  Whether someone kills me for wearing my Star of David, or whether they kill me because they want the $20 in my wallet, it doesn't matter.  I'm just as dead either way.  Violent criminals need to be stopped regardless of their motive.  Hate crimes just need to be addressed in the sense that our society needs education about different groups, and they need to realize that everyone is human.  Hate crimes are something that can be somewhat controlled IMO because education can curb the instances of these crimes.  JMO.<br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doublelatte>Double Latte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Got Milk?</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#3333ff>(3/13/03 6:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hate Crimes?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>people should be punished based off the crime itself as opposed to the motive.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
