<br>
&quot;Intention&quot; is quite relevant in these cases.<br>
<br>
Now as far as &quot;hate crime&quot; vs &quot;regular crime&quot;, I don't think it should matter who the victim was (white hetero or gay black), but the background/research on the perp. Does the perp's living quarters and previous convictions indicate a focused hate? A general hate? Situational stupidity?<br>
<br>
And I don't think the issue of conviction should hinge on the answer, but the question of &quot;rehabilitation&quot; [sic!] would come into play. (Which is a whole 'nuther ball-o-wax.)<br>
