I was only using crimes against blacks as an example.  There is no need for me to list every single group that is attacked.  Blacks have the highest number of hate crimes committed against them, so they were the easiest example.  As for hate crimes since 9/11, it isn't true that most of the hate crimes have been committed against Muslims.  Crimes against Muslims are on the rise, this is true, but they still pale in comparison to attacks against blacks and Jews.  That doesn't make them less tragic, I was just saying that your statement was inaccurate.  Assuming every hate crime logged is truly a hate crime, attacks against Jews are more than twice that of Muslims, and attacks against blacks are more than 6 times that of Muslims.  In 2002, there were 480 recorded attacks against Muslims, almost 1100 against Jews and almost 3,000 against blacks.  I had obtained that info some time ago on the Anti-Defamation League website.  I'm not sure what the number was for hate crimes against gays.  Like I said, I'm not trying to minimize attacks against Muslims, I was just correcting the statement.  <br>
